=== Etymology ===
Late [[Latin]] ''[[abbreviatio]]'': compare French [[abbréviation]]; from Latin ''[[ab]]'', '''from''', + ''[[brevis]]'', '''short''', + ending ''-atio'' indicating a verbal noun of action or process.

=== Noun ===
#The act of [[shortening]], or reducing.
#The result of [[abbreviating]]; an [[abridgment]]. - [[w:Tylor]]
#The form to which a word or phrase is reduced by contraction and [[omission]]; a letter or letters, standing for a word or phrase of which they are a part; as, ''Gen.'' for ''Genesis''; ''U.S.A.'' for ''United States of America''.
#''(Music):'' One dash, or more, through the stem of a note, [[dividing]] it [[respectively]] into [[quavers]], [[semiquavers]], [[demi-semiquavers]], or [[hemi-demi-semiquavers]]. - [[w:Moore]]

